title: 2005–06 Azerbaijan Cup
text:
The <a href="Azerbaijan%20Cup">Azerbaijan Cup</a> 2005–06 was the 14th season of the annual cup competition in <a href="Azerbaijan">Azerbaijan</a> with the <a href="%23Final">final</a> taking place on 3 June 2006. Sixteen teams competed in this year's competition. <a href="FK%20Baku">Baku</a> were the defending champions.
Round of 16.
The first legs were played on November 3 and 4 while the second legs were played on November 18 and 19, 2005.
Quarterfinals.
Three of the ties first legs were played on March 3 and 04, with their second legs being played on March 17 and 18, 2006. The exception to this was the <a href="FK%20MKT%20Araz">MKT Araz</a> vs <a href="FK%20Khazar%20Lankaran">Khazar-Lenkoran</a> tie which was played on April 24 and 27.
Semifinals.
The first legs were played on April 25 and May 3, 2006. The second legs were played on May 3 and 7, 2006.
